:: History {"position":"975,1050","size":"100,100"}
The World Heritage Convention, initiated by UNESCO in 1972, stemmed from mounting apprehensions regarding the rapid decay and loss of significant cultural and natural landmarks globally. Arising from the imperative to secure these invaluable assets for posterity, the convention sought to establish an international framework for their safeguarding and conservation. 


