:: Selection Criteria {"position":"1200,1050","size":"100,100"}
The most important details are that the site must have “outstanding universal value” and meet at least one of the ten criteria listed by Unesco:
stand in for a masterpiece of human creativity, 
exhibit a significant exchange of human values,
bear a unique testimony to a living or extinct cultural tradition or civilization,
be a magnificent embodiment of a certain building type, 
be a prime example of a traditional human settlement, 
have a direct or tangible relationship to historical occurrences,
have remarkable natural occurrences, 
be outstanding examples of major stages in human history,
 be outstanding cases of important ecological and biological processes,
contain the most significant and vital natural habitats for the in-situ conservation of biological diversity.



